North Carolina-Asheville Becomes First Team to Earn NCAA Tournament Bid

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-03-06T02:16:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-06/north-carolina-asheville-first-team-to-earn-ncaa-tournament-bid.html
The University of North Carolina-
Asheville defeated top-seeded Coastal Carolina University 60-47
to win the Big South Conference title game and earn the first
bid to the National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament.  Chris Stephenson scored 14 points for the third-seeded
Bulldogs, whose first and only berth in the NCAA tournament was
in 2003. Jaron Lane had 13 points and Matt Dickey added 12 at
Kimble Arena in Conway,  South Carolina .  Coastal Carolina, with 21 turnovers, lost todayâ€™s title
game for the second straight year. The Chanticleers (28-5, 16-2
Big South) will get an automatic bid to the National
Invitational Tournament.  Chad Gray led the Chanticleers with 13 points and Sam
McLaurin and Anthony Raffa each added 12 points.  To contact the reporter on this story:
